  Dialogue:
  - <i>Surprise</i> was the word that best defined what William felt when he heard
    that song, the skill that <color=#FF0080>Maduin</color> had with the flute was
    definitely impressive.
  - That sound was not only beautiful, it also brought a sense of harmony towards
    the world. Feeling the wind on his face, <color=purple>William</color> contemplated
    the immensity of the world and at the same time felt part of it.
  - All this thanks to that music.
  - Thanks to those soft lips gently blowing a flute.
  - Are you okay <color=purple>William</color>? You look kind of mesmerized.
  - I was just thinking... about that leaf, about nature... That's it! I'm thinking
    of nature and your music, good combination.
  - <color=#FF0080>Maduin</color> gave a sweet laugh.
  - You are beautiful when you feel ashamed.
  - I'm not feeling ashamed. Why would I?
  - Want to learn to play? <color=#FF0080>Maduin</color> approached his face and
    brought his flute to <color=purple>William</color>'s lips.
  - Why would I learn to play? I am an assassin, not a bard.
  - A lot of assassins work as bards in their spare time, the former guild leader
    became a bard after he retired, you know?
  - What's the point in that? What music has to do with murder?
  - The essence of music is in the feelings it arouses. Murder, war, justice and
    music, it's all about feelings.
  - 'Normally <color=purple>William</color> would scoff or criticize an idea he found
    as strange as this one. But some feeling was growing inside him and that feeling
    made him ask:'
  - Why?
  - Think of a war. Why does one side kill the other? Does each soldier have an extremely
    different view of morals, politics or justice from the enemy to the point where
    they are willing to kill or be killed?
  - I think not. What makes someone believe in a moral or a cause is not reason or
    logic, but fear or another very special feeling.
  - Think of our fight against the warriors. Warriors and assassins promote their
    respective wills by arousing the feeling of fear. People avoid breaking guild
    laws and Sarka's laws, simply because they fear death.
  - But there is another feeling that guides people, the feeling that bards cultivate,
    the feeling that beautiful music awakens, the feeling that I like best.
  - The word feeling echoed over and over in <color=purple>William</color>'s head,
    as if he had to solve a riddle.
  - That feeling is passion.
  - "Maybe\u2026"
  - Alright, I'll try to learn to play.
  DialogueBR:
  - "<i>Surpresa</i> era a palavra que melhor definia o que <color=purple>William</color>
    sentiu ao ouvir aquela m\xFAsica, a habilidade que <color=#FF0080>Maduin</color>
    tinha com a flauta era definitivamente impressionante."
  - "Aquele som n\xE3o era apenas belo, ele tamb\xE9m trazia um sentimento de harmonia
    em rela\xE7\xE3o ao mundo. Ao sentir o vento em seu rosto, <color=purple>William</color>
    contemplou a imensid\xE3o do mundo e ao mesmo tempo se sentiu parte dele."
  - "Tudo isso gra\xE7as \xE0quela m\xFAsica."
  - "Gra\xE7as \xE0queles l\xE1bios macios soprando gentilmente uma flauta."
  - "Tudo bem <color=purple>William</color>? Voc\xEA parece meio hipnotizado."
  - "Eu s\xF3 estava pensando\u2026 nessa folha, na natureza\u2026 Isso! Eu estou
    pensando na natureza e na sua m\xFAsica, boa combina\xE7\xE3o."
  - <color=#FF0080>Maduin</color> deu uma risada doce.
  - "Voc\xEA fica bonito quando sente vergonha."
  - "Eu n\xE3o estou sentindo vergonha. Por que eu sentiria?"
  - "Quer aprender a tocar? <color=#FF0080>Maduin</color> aproximou seu rosto e levou
    sua flauta at\xE9 os l\xE1bios de <color=purple>William</color>."
  - "Por que eu iria aprender a tocar? Eu sou um assassino, n\xE3o um bardo."
  - "Muitos assassinos trabalham como bardos nas horas vagas, o ex-l\xEDder da guilda
    se tornou um bardo depois que se aposentou, sabia?"
  - "Qual o sentido nisso? O que m\xFAsica tem a ver com assassinato?"
  - "A ess\xEAncia da m\xFAsica est\xE1 nos sentimentos que ela desperta. Assassinato,
    guerra, justi\xE7a e m\xFAsica, tudo isso \xE9 sobre sentimentos."
  - "Normalmente <color=purple>William</color> zombava ou criticava uma ideia que
    achava t\xE3o estranha quanto esta. Mas algum sentimento estava crescendo dentro
    dele e esse sentimento o fez perguntar:"
  - "Por qu\xEA?"
  - "Pense em uma guerra. Por que um lado mata o outro? Ser\xE1 que cada soldado
    possui uma vis\xE3o sobre moral, pol\xEDtica ou justi\xE7a extremamente diferente
    do inimigo a ponto deles estarem dispostos a matarem ou morrerem?\r\n"
  - "Eu acho que n\xE3o. O que faz algu\xE9m acreditar em uma moral ou em uma causa
    n\xE3o \xE9 a raz\xE3o ou a l\xF3gica, e sim o medo ou um outro sentimento muito
    especial."
  - "Pense na nossa luta contra os guerreiros. Os guerreiros e assassinos promovem
    suas respectivas vontades despertando o sentimento de medo. As pessoas evitam
    descumprir as leis da guilda e as leis de Sarka, simplesmente porque elas temem
    a morte.\r"
  - "Mas existe outro sentimento que guia as pessoas, o sentimento que os bardos
    cultivam, o sentimento que uma m\xFAsica bela desperta, o sentimento que eu mais
    gosto."
  - "A palavra sentimento ecoava v\xE1rias vezes na cabe\xE7a de <color=purple>William</color>,
    como se ele tivesse que solucionar um enigma."
  - "Esse sentimento \xE9 a paix\xE3o."
  - "Talvez\u2026 "
  - Tudo bem, eu vou tentar aprender a tocar.
